				\begin{document}$${\rm{Change}}\,{\rm{in}}\,{\rm{biomass}}=({{\rm{Biomass}}}_{{\rm{together}}}-{{\rm{Biomass}}}_{{\rm{monoculture}}})/({{\rm{Biomass}}}_{{\rm{monoculture}}}),$$\end{document}Changeinbiomass=(Biomasstogether−Biomassmonoculture)/(Biomassmonoculture),where Biomasstogether represents the mean value of individual aboveground biomass for each species when grown together with other species, and Biomassmonoculture represents the mean value of individual aboveground biomass for this species when grown in monoculture.
